replies.bodyText:
getOrCreateSpan takes Tracer as one of the input parameters.
public Span getOrCreateSpan(String name, Tracer tracer) 
Can't use startSpan because getting the span is needed in beforeExecution and onRequest is called inside afterMarshalling.  ExecutionInterceptor has its own lifecycle.

this spanName method is customizing the span name.  It is only used in the interceptor and nowhere else.
I also moved a few other helper methods related to AWS SDK lifecycle to the interceptor class.
@trask has created an issue to clean up AwsSdkClientTracer.  I think we all agreed that AWS SDK doesn't fit well with the HttpClientTracer pattern.
